            . My mother sent the prisoner to work at Mr. Chapman's house, in her place; I heard on the Tuesday following, that the spoon was missed - I asked the prisoner if she took it; she said, certainly she did - that she was very sorry - that she had done it through distress, and had pawned it at Mr. Jenkin's, Crawford-street, and she gave me the affidavit of it.</p>
